# Figma Import Conventions

## Workflow

1. **Receive Figma URL** → Use `implement-design` skill or Figma MCP to inspect the design
2. **Identify components** → Map to existing shadcn/ui components where possible
3. **Create custom components** → For unique UI elements, create in `src/components/custom/`
4. **Apply animations** → Use `@/components/animations/animated` wrapper for scroll reveals

## File Organization

```
src/components/
├── ui/          # shadcn/ui primitives (do not edit manually)
├── custom/      # Custom components from Figma UI kit
│   ├── hero-section.tsx
│   ├── feature-card.tsx
│   ├── pricing-table.tsx
│   ├── testimonial.tsx
│   └── cta-banner.tsx
├── layout/      # Header, footer, nav (shared across pages)
└── animations/  # Animation wrappers
```

## Naming Conventions

- Files: `kebab-case.tsx` (e.g., `hero-section.tsx`)
- Components: `PascalCase` (e.g., `HeroSection`)
- Props interfaces: `ComponentNameProps` (e.g., `HeroSectionProps`)

## Component Template

When creating a new component from Figma:

```tsx
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils'

interface ComponentNameProps {
  className?: string
  // ... props from Figma design
}

export function ComponentName({ className, ...props }: ComponentNameProps) {
  return (
    <div className={cn('base-styles', className)}>
      {/* Implementation */}
    </div>
  )
}
```

## Responsive Rules

- Every component MUST work on mobile (320px) through desktop (1440px+)
- Use `flex-col` on mobile, `flex-row` on desktop (md: or lg: breakpoint)
- Images: always include `sizes` prop with responsive breakpoints
- Typography: scale down on mobile (text-2xl → text-lg, etc.)
- Padding: use smaller values on mobile (px-4 → px-6 on lg:)

## Dark Mode

- Every component MUST support dark mode
- Use semantic color classes (bg-background, text-foreground) not hardcoded colors
- Test both light and dark variants
- If Figma provides dark mode designs, match exactly
- If not, rely on CSS variable system (automatic via .dark class)

## When Using Custom Figma UI Kit

- First check if shadcn/ui has an equivalent component
- If yes, use shadcn/ui and customize with className
- If no, create new component in `src/components/custom/`
- Custom components should accept `className` prop for composition
- Use CVA (class-variance-authority) for variant-based styling
